text:
Home / Headlines / Maria Kanellis heading back to WWE? Maria Kanellis heading back to WWE? Photo: WWE.com 
Former WWE Superstar Maria Kanellis and her husband Mike Bennett may be heading to the WWE. 
According to a new report from the Wrestling Observer ( via SE Scoops ), the pair have been ‘“very secretive” about where they are taking their talents next, which typically indicates WWE. 
This moves comes after Mike and Maria’s year run with Impact Wrestling, where they captured the Knockouts and X-Division Championship respectively, before officially departing from the company in February. 
Maria worked for the WWE from 2004 to 2010, debuting as part of the first televised Diva Search. She would later debut in Ring of Honor in late 2011 alongside Bennett, who was with ROH since 2008. 
Would you like to see Maria and Mike in the WWE? How would you book their return/debut? Who would you like to see the pair feud with? Let us know in the comments below! The Wrap (Febuary 25th, 2017): News from the week in women’s wrestling YonceLuvsDivas
